---
import SiteLayout from "../../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";

const schema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Article",
  "headline": "Income Tax Brackets by Country 2026",
  "description": "A comprehensive comparison of top marginal rates, effective taxes, and brackets across 46 global economies.",
  "author": {
    "@type": "Organization",
    "name": "firemaths.info"
  },
  "publisher": {
    "@type": "Organization",
    "name": "firemaths.info"
  },
  "datePublished": "2026-01-01",
  "dateModified": "2026-01-01"
};
---

<SiteLayout
  site="firemaths"
  title="Income Tax Brackets by Country 2026 | firemaths.info"
  description=""
  canonical="https://firemaths.info/tax-brackets-comparison" schema={schema}
>
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-8">
    

    <main id="app-root" class="space-y-6">
      <!-- Data will be injected here -->
    </main>

    <div class="bg-[var(--card-bg)] border border-[var(--border-color)] rounded-xl p-8 mb-8 methodology-container">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Methodology</h2>
      <p class="text-[var(--text-secondary)] mb-4">This 2026 comparative study analyzes personal income tax systems across 46 major economies. Data collection and validation processes included:</p>
      <ul class="text-[var(--text-secondary)] list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
        <li><strong>Primary Sources:</strong> Data was systematically aggregated from PwC Tax Summaries, OECD statistical databases, Worldwide-Tax.com, TradingEconomics, and Tax-Rates.org.</li>
        <li><strong>Standardization:</strong> All local currency bracket thresholds were converted to USD to provide a unified comparative baseline. Effective tax rates at $50k and $100k thresholds include standard deductions but exclude complex specialized credits.</li>
        <li><strong>Scope:</strong> The analysis captures top marginal rates, lowest non-zero brackets, capital gains taxes, VAT/GST rates, and employee social security contributions.</li>
        <li><strong>Validation:</strong> Rates were strictly validated against known international maximums (0-65% for income, up to $2M USD for top bracket entry thresholds).</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-[var(--card-bg)] border border-[var(--border-color)] rounded-xl p-8 faq-container">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <div class="border-b border-[var(--border-color)] pb-6 mb-6 last:border-0 last:pb-0 last:mb-0 faq-item">
        <div class="text-lg font-bold text-[var(--accent-color)] mb-2 faq-question">Which country has the highest income tax?</div>
        <div class="text-[var(--text-secondary)] faq-answer">Sweden and Denmark consistently rank among the highest for top marginal personal income tax rates, often exceeding 52%. However, these top rates often apply at relatively lower income thresholds compared to countries like the US, resulting in a higher overall tax burden for middle-to-high earners.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="border-b border-[var(--border-color)] pb-6 mb-6 last:border-0 last:pb-0 last:mb-0 faq-item">
        <div class="text-lg font-bold text-[var(--accent-color)] mb-2 faq-question">What are the US federal tax brackets for 2026?</div>
        <div class="text-[var(--text-secondary)] faq-answer">For 2026, the US federal tax system remains progressive with 7 brackets ranging from 10% up to a top marginal rate of 37%. Note that state taxes (ranging from 0% in states like Texas and Florida to over 13% in California) apply additionally to these federal rates.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="border-b border-[var(--border-color)] pb-6 mb-6 last:border-0 last:pb-0 last:mb-0 faq-item">
        <div class="text-lg font-bold text-[var(--accent-color)] mb-2 faq-question">Do any countries have 0% income tax?</div>
        <div class="text-[var(--text-secondary)] faq-answer">Yes, several Middle Eastern countries including the United Arab Emirates and Saudi Arabia levy 0% personal income tax on salaries. However, these nations typically generate revenue through other means, such as VAT (usually 5-15%) and corporate taxes.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="border-b border-[var(--border-color)] pb-6 mb-6 last:border-0 last:pb-0 last:mb-0 faq-item">
        <div class="text-lg font-bold text-[var(--accent-color)] mb-2 faq-question">How does Canada's tax rate compare to the US?</div>
        <div class="text-[var(--text-secondary)] faq-answer">Canada's top federal marginal rate is 33%, but combined with provincial taxes, the top marginal rate can exceed 50% in provinces like Ontario and Quebec. The US top federal rate is 37%, and combined with state taxes, peaks around 50% in California. Canada generally offers more generous social safety nets funded by these taxes, but lacks the income splitting (joint filing) benefits available to US married couples.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="border-b border-[var(--border-color)] pb-6 mb-6 last:border-0 last:pb-0 last:mb-0 faq-item">
        <div class="text-lg font-bold text-[var(--accent-color)] mb-2 faq-question">What is the average tax rate in Europe?</div>
        <div class="text-[var(--text-secondary)] faq-answer">The average top marginal income tax rate across European OECD countries is approximately 42%. Western and Northern European nations (like France, Germany, and Norway) tend to have higher progressive rates, while Eastern European nations (like Romania and Hungary) frequently utilize lower, flat-tax systems (10-15%).</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <script is:inline>
// We fetch the data from our static JSON file that was generated during the build/pre-step.
    // Given the constraints of a pure static site without a build step for this specific HTML,
    // we fetch it dynamically on load.

    let rawData = [];
    let currentSort = { column: 'topMarginalRate', direction: 'desc' };

    async function init() {
      try {
        const response = await fetch('/data/tax-brackets-comparison.json');
        if (!response.ok) throw new Error('Failed to load data');
        rawData = await response.json();
        renderApp();
      } catch (err) {
        document.getElementById('app-root').innerHTML = `
          <div class="bg-[var(--card-bg)] border border-[var(--border-color)] rounded-xl p-8 text-center text-red-500">
            <h2>Error Loading Data</h2>
            <p>Could not load the tax comparison data. Please try again later.</p>
          </div>
        `;
        console.error(err);
      }
    }

    function renderApp() {
      const root = document.getElementById('app-root');

      const sortedData = [...rawData].sort((a, b) => {
        let valA = a[currentSort.column];
        let valB = b[currentSort.column];

        if (typeof valA === 'string') valA = valA.toLowerCase();
        if (typeof valB === 'string') valB = valB.toLowerCase();

        if (valA < valB) return currentSort.direction === 'asc' ? -1 : 1;
        if (valA > valB) return currentSort.direction === 'asc' ? 1 : -1;
        return 0;
      });

      const tableHTML = `
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 mb-8 controls">
          <div class="flex flex-col gap-2 input-group">
            <label class="text-sm font-semibold text-[var(--text-secondary)]">Search Country</label>
            <input type="text" id="searchInput" placeholder="e.g. United States" oninput="filterTable()" class="bg-[var(--bg-color)] border border-[var(--border-color)] text-white px-4 py-3 rounded-lg focus:outline-none focus:border-[var(--accent-color)]">
          </div>
          <div class="flex flex-col gap-2 input-group">
            <label class="text-sm font-semibold text-[var(--text-secondary)]">Region</label>
            <select id="regionFilter" onchange="filterTable()" class="bg-[var(--bg-color)] border border-[var(--border-color)] text-white px-4 py-3 rounded-lg focus:outline-none focus:border-[var(--accent-color)]">
              <option value="all">All Regions</option>
              ${[...new Set(rawData.map(d => d.region))].sort().map(r => `<option value="${r}">${r}</option>`).join('')}
            </select>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-[var(--card-bg)] border border-[var(--border-color)] rounded-xl p-8 overflow-x-auto data-table-container">
          <table id="taxTable" class="w-full text-left border-collapse min-w-[800px]">
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th onclick="handleSort('country')" class="p-4 border-b border-[var(--border-color)] font-bold text-[var(--text-secondary)] whitespace-nowrap cursor-pointer hover:text-[var(--accent-color)] transition-colors">Country ${getSortIcon('country')}</th>
                <th onclick="handleSort('topMarginalRate')" class="p-4 border-b border-[var(--border-color)] font-bold text-[var(--text-secondary)] whitespace-nowrap cursor-pointer hover:text-[var(--accent-color)] transition-colors">Top Rate ${getSortIcon('topMarginalRate')}</th>
                <th onclick="handleSort('topBracketStartUSD')" class="p-4 border-b border-[var(--border-color)] font-bold text-[var(--text-secondary)] whitespace-nowrap cursor-pointer hover:text-[var(--accent-color)] transition-colors">Top Bracket Starts (USD) ${getSortIcon('topBracketStartUSD')}</th>
                <th onclick="handleSort('lowestRate')" class="p-4 border-b border-[var(--border-color)] font-bold text-[var(--text-secondary)] whitespace-nowrap cursor-pointer hover:text-[var(--accent-color)] transition-colors">Lowest Rate ${getSortIcon('lowestRate')}</th>
                <th onclick="handleSort('effectiveRateAt100kUSD')" class="p-4 border-b border-[var(--border-color)] font-bold text-[var(--text-secondary)] whitespace-nowrap cursor-pointer hover:text-[var(--accent-color)] transition-colors">Effective Rate ($100k) ${getSortIcon('effectiveRateAt100kUSD')}</th>
                <th onclick="handleSort('capitalGainsTax')" class="p-4 border-b border-[var(--border-color)] font-bold text-[var(--text-secondary)] whitespace-nowrap cursor-pointer hover:text-[var(--accent-color)] transition-colors">Capital Gains ${getSortIcon('capitalGainsTax')}</th>
                <th onclick="handleSort('vatRate')" class="p-4 border-b border-[var(--border-color)] font-bold text-[var(--text-secondary)] whitespace-nowrap cursor-pointer hover:text-[var(--accent-color)] transition-colors">VAT / GST ${getSortIcon('vatRate')}</th>
                <th class="p-4 border-b border-[var(--border-color)] font-bold text-[var(--text-secondary)] whitespace-nowrap">Notes</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              ${sortedData.map(d => `
                <tr class="data-row hover:bg-[color-mix(in_srgb,var(--accent-color)_5%,transparent)] transition-colors" data-country="${d.country.toLowerCase()}" data-region="${d.region}">
                  <td class="p-4 border-b border-[var(--border-color)] font-bold text-white">${d.country}</td>
                  <td class="p-4 border-b border-[var(--border-color)] font-mono text-[var(--accent-color)] font-bold">${d.topMarginalRate}%</td>
                  <td class="p-4 border-b border-[var(--border-color)] font-mono text-white">$${d.topBracketStartUSD.toLocaleString()}</td>
                  <td class="p-4 border-b border-[var(--border-color)] font-mono text-white">${d.lowestRate}%</td>
                  <td class="p-4 border-b border-[var(--border-color)] font-mono text-white">${d.effectiveRateAt100kUSD}%</td>
                  <td class="p-4 border-b border-[var(--border-color)] font-mono text-white">${d.capitalGainsTax}%</td>
                  <td class="p-4 border-b border-[var(--border-color)] font-mono text-white">${d.vatRate}%</td>
                  <td class="p-4 border-b border-[var(--border-color)] text-sm text-[var(--text-secondary)] max-w-[250px]">${d.specialNotes || '-'}</td>
                </tr>
              `).join('')}
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      `;

      root.innerHTML = tableHTML;
    }

    function getSortIcon(column) {
      if (currentSort.column !== column) return '<span class="text-[var(--border-color)]">↕</span>';
      return currentSort.direction === 'asc' ? '↑' : '↓';
    }

    window.handleSort = function(column) {
      if (currentSort.column === column) {
        currentSort.direction = currentSort.direction === 'asc' ? 'desc' : 'asc';
      } else {
        currentSort.column = column;
        currentSort.direction = 'asc';
      }
      renderApp();
      filterTable(); // re-apply filters after re-render
    };

    window.filterTable = function() {
      const search = document.getElementById('searchInput').value.toLowerCase();
      const region = document.getElementById('regionFilter').value;
      const rows = document.querySelectorAll('.data-row');

      rows.forEach(row => {
        const countryMatch = row.getAttribute('data-country').includes(search);
        const regionMatch = region === 'all' || row.getAttribute('data-region') === region;
        row.style.display = (countryMatch && regionMatch) ? '' : 'none';
      });
    };

    // Initialize the app
    document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', init);
  </script>

  <!-- Pillar Guide Link -->
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-5 pt-8 pb-12">
    <div class="border-t border-[var(--border-color)] pt-8">
      <p class="text-xs font-bold text-[var(--accent-color)] tracking-wide uppercase mb-2">📚 Complete Guide</p>
      <a href="/guide-taxes-complete" class="block bg-[var(--card-bg)] border border-[var(--border-color)] rounded-xl p-5 hover:border-[var(--accent-color)] hover:-translate-y-0.5 transition-all">
        <h3 class="text-base font-bold text-white">Understanding Your Taxes: A Complete Guide</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-[var(--text-secondary)] mt-1">Read the full guide →</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</SiteLayout>
